The paper deals with binary search trees and their access sequences, which are fundamental data structures and algorithms topics falling under the category of data structures (cs.DS). The use of forbidden submatrix theory suggests a connection to combinatorics (cs.DM). The paper also involves analyzing the complexity of access sequences, which could fall under computational complexity (cs.CC). The concept of pattern avoidance is also related to graph theory (cs.GT) and information theory (cs.IT).
